should be ticketed against gazebo or rqt_gui (asked Dirk, he says non-ROS manifest files have no business being in the ROS_PACKAGE_PATH).  ", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>If I use the setup.sh script as described in the <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"http://gazebosim.org/wiki/InstallDRC\" rel=\"nofollow\">drcsim install instructions</a>, the model directories are added to the ROS_PACKAGE_PATH. This causes errors in rqt_gui's plugin loader, as it apparently reads the manifest and does not find the expected (ROS) entries there (see attached file). It can perhaps be argued if this should be ticketed against gazebo or rqt_gui (asked Dirk, he says non-ROS manifest files have no business being in the ROS_PACKAGE_PATH).  </p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "state": "closed", "version": {"name": "all", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/225575.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2012-10-30T01:33:55.340108+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-09-14T19:43:45.468013+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 162}